Leaders from China and several African countries are meeting in the Senegalese capital of Dakar for the 8th Ministerial Conference of the Forum on China-Africa Cooperation (FOCAC). The FOCAC is an important institutional guarantee for China-Africa cooperation, and it is clear that China-Africa cooperation will blossom and flourish under this mechanism. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Aaron Liu explains how friendly bilateral ties have been helping China and Africa to reap rich global dividends in trade matters.